.B
\fBkex_alg() ::\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group-exchange-sha256' |\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group14-sha256' |\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group16-sha512' |\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group18-sha512' | 'curve25519-sha256' |\fR
\fB          'curve25519-sha256@libssh.org' | 'curve448-sha512' |\fR
\fB          'ecdh-sha2-nistp256' | 'ecdh-sha2-nistp384' |\fR
\fB          'ecdh-sha2-nistp521' | 'mlkem768x25519-sha256' |\fR
\fB          legacy_kex_alg().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBkey_cb_common_option() ::\fR
\fB          {key_cb,\fR
\fB           Module :: atom() | {Module :: atom(), Opts :: [term()]}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Module implementing the behaviour \fIssh_client_key_api\fR and/or \fIssh_server_key_api\fR. Can be used to customize the handling of public keys. If callback options are provided along with the module name, they are made available to the callback module via the options passed to it under the key 'key_cb_private'.

.PP
The \fIOpts\fR defaults to \fI[]\fR when only the \fIModule\fR is specified.

.PP
The default value of this option is \fI{ssh_file, []}\fR. See also the manpage of \fIssh_file\fR.

.PP
A call to the call-back function \fIF\fR will be

.IP
.nf
	  Module:F(..., [{key_cb_private,Opts}|UserOptions])

.fi

.PP
where \fI...\fR are arguments to \fIF\fR as in \fIssh_client_key_api\fR and/or \fIssh_server_key_api\fR. The \fIUserOptions\fR are the options given to ssh:connect, ssh:shell or ssh:daemon.


.RE
.B
\fBlegacy_cipher_alg() ::\fR
\fB          'aes128-cbc' | 'aes192-cbc' | 'aes256-cbc' | '3des-cbc'.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBlegacy_kex_alg() ::\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group1-sha1' | 'diffie-hellman-group14-sha1' |\fR
\fB          'diffie-hellman-group-exchange-sha1'.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBlegacy_mac_alg() :: 'hmac-sha1-96'.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBlegacy_pubkey_alg() :: 'ssh-rsa' | 'ssh-dss'.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBlimit_bytes() :: non_neg_integer() | infinity.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBlimit_time() :: pos_integer() | infinity.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the limit when rekeying is to be initiated. Both the max time and max amount of data could be configured:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI{Minutes, Bytes}\fR initiate rekeying when any of the limits are reached.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIBytes\fR initiate rekeying when \fIBytes\fR number of bytes are transferred, or at latest after one hour.

.RE

.PP
When a rekeying is done, both the timer and the byte counter are restarted. Defaults to one hour and one GByte.

.PP
If \fIMinutes\fR is set to \fIinfinity\fR, no rekeying will ever occur due to that max time has passed. Setting \fIBytes\fR to \fIinfinity\fR will inhibit rekeying after a certain amount of data has been transferred. If the option value is set to \fI{infinity, infinity}\fR, no rekeying will be initiated. Note that rekeying initiated by the peer will still be performed.


.RE
.B
\fBmac_alg() ::\fR
\fB          'hmac-sha1' | 'hmac-sha1-etm@openssh.com' | 'hmac-sha2-256' |\fR
\fB          'hmac-sha2-512' | 'hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com' |\fR
\fB          'hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com' |\fR
\fB          disabled_mac_alg() |\fR
\fB          legacy_mac_alg().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBmax_idle_time_common_option() :: {idle_time, timeout()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets a time-out on a connection when no channels are open. Defaults to \fIinfinity\fR. The unit is milliseconds.

.PP
The timeout is not active until channels are started, so it does not limit the time from the connection creation to the first channel opening.

.PP
For more information about timeouts, see the Timeouts section in the User's Guide Hardening chapter.


.RE
.B
\fBmax_initial_idle_time_daemon_option() ::\fR
\fB          {max_initial_idle_time, timeout()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Maximum time in milliseconds for the first channel start after completion of the authentication negotiation. Defaults to \fIinfinity\fR.

.PP
For more information about timeouts, see the Timeouts section in the User's Guide Hardening chapter.


.RE
.B
\fBmax_log_item_len_common_option() ::\fR
\fB          {max_log_item_len, limit_bytes()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets a limit for the size of a logged item excluding a header. The unit is bytes and the value defaults to 500.


.RE
.B
\fBmod_args() :: {Module :: atom(), Args :: list()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBmod_fun_args() ::\fR
\fB          {Module :: atom(), Function :: atom(), Args :: list()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBmodify_algorithms_common_option() ::\fR
\fB          {modify_algorithms, modify_algs_list()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBmodify_algs_list() ::\fR
\fB          [{append, algs_list()} |\fR
\fB           {prepend, algs_list()} |\fR
\fB           {rm, algs_list()}].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Modifies the list of algorithms to use in the algorithm negotiation. The modifications are applied after the option \fIpreferred_algorithms\fR (if existing) is applied.

.PP
The algorithm for modifications works like this:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Input is the \fImodify_algs_list/0\fR and a set of algorithms \fIA\fR obtained from the \fIpreferred_algorithms\fR option if existing, or else from the ssh:default_algorithms/0.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
The head of the \fImodify_algs_list/0\fR modifies \fIA\fR giving the result \fIA'\fR.

.PP
The possible modifications are:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Append or prepend supported but not enabled algorithm(s) to the list of algorithms. If the wanted algorithms already are in \fIA\fR they will first be removed and then appended or prepended,

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Remove (rm) one or more algorithms from \fIA\fR.

.RE

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Repeat the modification step with the tail of \fImodify_algs_list/0\fR and the resulting \fIA'\fR.

.RE

.PP
If an unsupported algorithm is in the \fImodify_algs_list/0\fR, it will be silently ignored

.PP
If there are more than one modify_algorithms options, the result is undefined.

.PP
Here is an example of this option:

.IP
.nf
	  {modify_algorithms,
	  [{prepend, [{kex, ['diffie-hellman-group1-sha1']}],
	  {rm,      [{compression, [none]}]}
	  ]
	  }

.fi

.PP
The example specifies that:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
the old key exchange algorithm 'diffie-hellman-group1-sha1' should be the main alternative. It will be the main alternative since it is prepened to the list

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
The compression algorithm none (= no compression) is removed so compression is enforced

.RE

.PP
For background and more examples see the User's Guide.


.RE
.B
\fBnegotiation_timeout_daemon_option() ::\fR
\fB          {negotiation_timeout, timeout()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Maximum time in milliseconds for the authentication negotiation. Defaults to 120000 ms (2 minutes). If the client fails to log in within this time, the connection is closed.

.PP
For more information about timeouts, see the Timeouts section in the User's Guide Hardening chapter.


.RE
.B
\fBopen_socket() :: gen_tcp:socket().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The socket is supposed to be result of a gen_tcp:connect or a gen_tcp:accept. The socket must be in passive mode (that is, opened with the option \fI{active,false})\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBpref_public_key_algs_common_option() ::\fR
\fB          {pref_public_key_algs, [pubkey_alg()]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
List of user (client) public key algorithms to try to use.

.PP
The default value is the \fIpublic_key\fR entry in the list returned by ssh:default_algorithms/0.

.PP
If there is no public key of a specified type available, the corresponding entry is ignored. Note that the available set is dependent on the underlying cryptolib and current user's public keys.

.PP
See also the option \fIuser_dir\fR for specifying the path to the user's keys.


.RE
.B
\fBpreferred_algorithms_common_option() ::\fR
\fB          {preferred_algorithms, algs_list()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBprofile_common_option() :: {profile, atom()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Used together with \fIip-address\fR and \fIport\fR to uniquely identify a ssh daemon. This can be useful in a virtualized environment, where there can be more that one server that has the same \fIip-address\fR and \fIport\fR. If this property is not explicitly set, it is assumed that the the \fIip-address\fR and \fIport\fR uniquely identifies the SSH daemon.


.RE
